					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>States that <hi rend="bold">Māra,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Īśvara-Nāyaka,</hi> minister of the <hi rend="bold">Chōḍa</hi> chief <hi rend="bold">Kannāradēva</hi> got two tanks excavated and the image of Sōmīśvara established in the village of <hi rend="bold">Koppa[ram]</hi> in <hi rend="bold">Kammanāṇḍu</hi> and that <hi rend="bold">Kannāradēva's</hi> brother <hi rend="bold">Chōḍa-Balli</hi> made a gift of the village of <hi rend="bold">Biḍepalli</hi> to the said temple.</p>						

						<p>Face A.</p>						

						</summary>
